        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 6:29PM CDT by NWS Kansas City/Pleasant Hill MO</headline>
        <description>At 628 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Drexel, or 8 miles southeast of Louisburg, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Adrian, Garden City, Archie, and Drexel.

This includes Interstate 49 between mile markers 141 and 155.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Missouri.</instruction>
